author: News Tribune
title: Fatima claims district title in boys soccer
text:
Share 
ST. CLAIR, Mo. — It took penalty kicks to decide the Class 2 District 10 title game Thursday night between the Fatima Comets and Sullivan Eagles. 
Fatima claimed the crown, outscoring Sullivan 3-1 in the round to advance by a score of 1-0 to sectional action. The goals were scored by Chad Angerer, Luke Rehagen and Josh Kunkleman. 
Kunkleman was in goal in the shutout for Fatima. 
Fatima (13-13) will play District 9 champion Southern Boone on Tuesday in Ashland. Southern Boone (23-1-1) defeated Boonville 1-0 to win its district title. ﻿
